    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Logan County Bail Bonds FAQ</h2>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;">
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How do I bail someone out of Logan County Jail in Guthrie?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Call Angel Bail Bonds at (405) 614-3000 any time, day or night. We handle Logan County bonds daily and can often post remotely. The Logan County Jail is at 216 S. Broad St, Guthrie, OK 73044. Phone: (405) 282-4100. Once we post the bond, most releases take 1-4 hours.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How much does a bail bond cost in Logan County?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Oklahoma bail bond premiums are regulated by state law. Angel Bail Bonds offers competitive rates with multiple payment options: cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, Venmo, and financing for qualifying clients. Call us at (405) 614-3000 for a free quote on any Logan County bond.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How long does release from Logan County Jail take?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">After Angel Bail Bonds posts the bond, most defendants are released from Logan County Jail within 1-4 hours. Actual release time depends on jail staffing levels, time of day, and current booking volume. We work to expedite every release.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">When are Logan County arraignments?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Arraignments are held Tuesdays and Thursdays at 1:30 PM at the Logan County Courthouse, 301 E. Harrison St, Guthrie, OK 73044. Call the Court Clerk at (405) 282-0123 between 8:00 AM and 10:30 AM on the same day to get on the docket.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">Can I post bail from Stillwater for a Logan County arrest?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Yes. Angel Bail Bonds is based in Stillwater, just 33 miles from the Logan County Jail in Guthrie. We can often handle the entire process remotely by phone. You provide the inmate details and payment, and we coordinate directly with the jail.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">Does Angel Bail Bonds serve Crescent, Coyle, and Mulhall?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Yes. We serve every community in Logan County, including Guthrie, Crescent, Coyle, Mulhall, Orlando, Marshall, Cedar Valley, Cimarron City, and Meridian. Anyone arrested within Logan County is booked at the Logan County Jail in Guthrie, and we can post bond there 24/7.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">What payment methods are accepted for Logan County bail bonds?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Angel Bail Bonds accepts cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, and Venmo. We also offer financing plans for clients who qualify. Our goal is to remove financial barriers so your loved one can be released from Logan County Jail as quickly as possible. Call (405) 614-3000 to discuss payment options.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NEIGHBORING COUNTIES -->
  <section style="padding: 24px 1.5rem 0; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px;">Neighboring Counties We Serve</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/payne-county-jail-bail-bonds" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; padding: 6px 14px; background: var(--slate-50); border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;">Payne County →</a>
        <a href="/noble-county-bail-bonds" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; padding: 6px 14px; background: var(--slate-50); border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;">Noble County →</a>
        <a href="/lincoln-county-bail-bonds" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; padding: 6px 14px; background: var(--slate-50); border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;">Lincoln County →</a>
        <a href="/kay-county-bail-bonds" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; padding: 6px 14px; background: var(--slate-50); border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;">Kay County →</a>
